Sentencas: Single-layer ceramic fuel cells consisting of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2, Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 and a eutectic mixture of Li2CO3, Na2CO3 and K2CO3, were fabricated through extrusion-based 3D printing.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The sintering temperature of the printed cells was varied from 700 degrees C to 1000 degrees C to identify the optimal thermal treatment to maximize the cell performance.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It was found that the 3D printed single-layer cell sintered at 900 degrees C produced the highest power density (230 mW/cm(2)) at 550 degrees C, which is quite close to the performance (240 mW/cm(2)) of the single-layer cell fabricated through a conventional pressing method.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The best printed cell still had high ohmic (0.46 ohm center dot cm(2)) and polarization losses (0.32 ohm center dot cm(2)) based on EIS measurements conducted in an open-circuit condition.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The XRD spectra showed the characteristic peaks of the crystalline structures in the composite material.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: HR-TEM, SEM and EDS measurements revealed the morphological information of the composite materials and the distribution of the elements, respectively.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The BET surface area of the single-layer cells was found to decrease from 2.93 m(2)/g to 0.18 m(2)/g as the sintering temperature increased from 700 degrees C to 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The printed cell sintered at 900 degrees C had a BET surface area of 0.34 m(2)/g.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The fabrication of single-layer ceramic cells through up-scalable 3D technology could facilitate the scaling up and commercialization of this promising fuel cell technology.
Titulo: Systematic Analysis on the Effect of Sintering Temperature for Optimized Performance of Li0.15Ni0.45Zn0.4O2-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-Li2CO3-Na2CO3-K2CO3 Based 3D Printed Single-Layer Ceramic Fuel Cell
